Yes, but according to this:<br /><div class="quotetitle">blargg wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Frame interrupt flag is set three times in a row 29831 clocks after writing $00 to $4017.<br /></div><br /><br />In other words, yup, the PPU takes 341*262/3 CPU cycles per frame, but the APU doesn't rely in such timing (frame IRQs).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=39">Zepper</a> — Sat Jun 18, 2011 4:18 pm</p><hr />
